		{
			"type": "patchouli:text",
			"title": "Beneath Crops",
			"text": "The $(thing)Beneath$() may be a harsh environment, but it is still possible to find crops there. Beneath crops are incredibly resilient and can grow in extreme heat conditions making them useful for surviving below the Earth and on the surface."
		},
		{
			"type": "patchouli:text",
			"text": "Crops in the beneath behave just the same as crops on the surface, they have hydration, temperature, and nutrient requirements. You can even plant them in $(thing)Greenhouse$() planters or automate them in the $(thing)Electric Greenhouse$()!"
		},
